### Health check
GET http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/health

### Create inbox with explicit name
POST http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/emails/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "demo123",
  "domain": "temp.example.com",
  "expiryTime": 86400000
}

### Create inbox without name
POST http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/emails/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "domain": "temp.example.com",
  "expiryTime": 86400000
}

### Create inbox with blank name
POST http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/emails/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "   ",
  "domain": "temp.example.com",
  "expiryTime": 86400000
}

### List inboxes
GET http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/emails

### temp_mail admin create address
POST http://127.0.0.1:3000/admin/new_address
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
x-admin-auth: YOUR_ADMIN_PASSWORD

{
  "enablePrefix": true,
  "name": "demo1",
  "domain": "temp.example.com"
}

### temp_mail list mails via admin endpoint
GET http://127.0.0.1:3000/admin/mails?limit=1&offset=0
x-admin-auth: YOUR_ADMIN_PASSWORD

### temp_mail list mails for one address via admin endpoint
GET http://127.0.0.1:3000/admin/mails?limit=20&offset=0&address=test@example.com
x-admin-auth: YOUR_ADMIN_PASSWORD

### temp_mail list mails via bearer token
GET http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/mails
Authorization: Bearer SOME_USER_TOKEN

### temp_mail read one mail via bearer token
GET http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/mails/msg_1
Authorization: Bearer SOME_USER_TOKEN

### temp_mail list mails by address without bearer token
GET http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/mails?address=test@example.com
